
[1]fatherly

   F'ATHERLY, a. [father and like.]

   1. Like a father in affection and care; tender; paternal; protecting;
   careful; as fatherly care or affection.

   2. Pertaining to a father.

                 F'ATHERLY, adv. In the manner of a father.

   Thus Adam, fatherly displeased. [Not proper.]
